====Etymology====
OE. addere, naddere, eddre, AS. nædre, adder, snake; akin to OS. nadra, OHG. natra, natara, Ger. natter, Goth. nadrs, Icel. naðr, masc., naðra, fem.: cf. W. neidr, Gorn. naddyr, Ir. nathair, L. natrix, water  snake.  (Resulted from misdivision of "a nadder" to "an adder".)

====Meanings====
# (Obsolete) a snake.
# (British) A small venomous [[serpent]] of the genus [[Vipera]]. The  common European adder is the ''Vipera'' (or ''Pelias'') ''berus''. The puff adders of Africa are species of the genus ''[[Clotho]]''.
# (American) Any of several small nonvenomous snakes resembling the adder, such as the milk snake.

